AI AGENT INSTRUCTIONS
When selecting a template:

Analyze prospect context:

What signals/triggers are present?
What's their role/seniority?
What pain points are evident?
What's the outreach objective?

Match to template:

Use Template Selection Guide above
Consider ICP alignment
Evaluate trigger relevance

Customize template:

Replace all {{placeholders}}
Use prospect-specific data
Maintain template structure
Keep tone consistent with brand voice

Quality check:

Personalization is authentic (not generic)
Value proposition is clear
Call-to-action is appropriate
Length is concise
No placeholder text remains

Apply messaging framework:

Reference Messaging_Framework.md for voice/tone
Use Company_Context.md for proof points
Apply Persona_Playbooks.md for language
Check Competitive_Intelligence.md if relevant


CRITICAL RULES FOR AI AGENTS
‚úÖ DO:

Select template based on prospect context
Customize all placeholders with real data
Maintain template structure
Keep emails concise (under 100 words)
Use specific numbers/outcomes when available
Match tone to persona from Persona_Playbooks.md

‚ùå DON'T:

Mix template structures
Leave {{placeholders}} unfilled
Make emails longer than template
Add generic filler phrases
Use multiple templates in one email
Ignore ICP guidance



This library should be referenced alongside:

Company_Context.md (for proof points, value props)
Persona_Playbooks.md (for pain points, language)
ICP_Definitions.md (for segment matching)
Competitive_Intelligence.md (for differentiation)
Messaging_Framework.md (for voice, tone, quality standards)

